      <p>Beautiful post with such a warm memory. All the cherry clafloutis recipes say that in France, the only real way to serve clafloutis is not to pit the cherries, and place a small dish for your guests to spit the pits into. I personally think that makes for a lousy host. Love the idea of the brown sugared pears, and can hardly wait until next May for a rhubarb clafloutis. (And your new book!)</p>
